1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:10,168
With enable.idempotence=true, each producer instance receives a Producer ID (PID) from the broker.

2
00:00:10,118 --> 00:00:16,631
Every batch is tagged with a monotonically increasing sequence number per partition.

3
00:00:16,631 --> 00:00:31,671
If the producer retries a failed send, the broker compares the incoming sequence number against what it last wrote and silently discards duplicates — exactly-once at the producer level within a session.

4
00:00:31,671 --> 00:00:36,500
Everyone says Python Implementation is the best approach.

5
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:41,105
That is , actually wrong for most real-world systems.

6
00:00:41,105 --> 00:00:44,131
I will show you why in a moment.

